race.description: Hallam Truck Centre Leila Rose Foundation Hcp
race.comment: HURRY CURRY (6) can be an improver third up. The fresh run with a big weight was good before an even effort in a sit and sprint at Cranbourne. That should give her the ideal platform to peak third up on the bigger track and she does drop a grade for this. SUNTORA (11) found her race out to 1800m last start at Caulfield Heath and destroyed her rivals by 4.5 lengths in good time. No issue this trip, she gets in light and can measure up. POLITELY DUN (7) and PRINCE ERIC (3) both back up from a BM84 at Ballarat last week. That was a shifty track, POLITELY DUN never got into the race which PRINCE ERIC won. Both have claims, the former is going better than it looks. EYE FOR AN EYE (10) has won both this time in and has to be respected.
